cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SE

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it focuses on detecting and characterizing malware delivery networks and their tactics for evading detection. The use of unsupervised machine learning techniques also suggests a potential fit with the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The study of download events and network behavior could also fall under the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category. The use of novel techniques and empirical observations may align with the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the development of the Beewolf system for detecting silent delivery campaigns could potentially fit with the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category.
